My Japan trip has officially came to an end and I just want to say this. 

Thank you. Thank you to any and everyone who has ever supported me. I would never be able to live this sick life without people who support me on any capacity. 7 years ago I was working a dead end job at a mall and I was sick of it. I started streaming and making dumb videos and somehow people enjoyed it. I have became friends with people who are my heroes, have fun doing something I love, and most importantly, be me… You guys have allowed me to meet so many beautiful people and see so many beautiful things. In the last month I was in a commercial, got to travel the world with someone I love, see my best friend get 3rd place at a world championship, and see a country I’m so fucking fortunate to see and most won’t be lucky enough to see, and a part of me feels guilty about it. My heart is so full and I’ll always be in debt to you guys. I can’t wait to be back and get back to spending time with you guys. I will never be able to repay you for the love and opportunities you have given me. You’ve allowed me to live this dream, and I don’t plan on waking up anytime soon. 

Stick Tight.
